Commissioning artists for various non-porny projects is REALLY hard. A lot of them either never get back to you or just disappear after an initial e-mail, many of them on social media are bait and switch scammers, and the real ones want between $800-$3000 for a single image in a minimal style. The ones who don't fucking suck and are clearly some 20 year old who learned photoshop in some community college, but try to convince you they can do what you want despite having a dogshit portfolio.

I FINALLY found an artist who didn't flake, was reasonably priced, and actually made what she said she could, but she wanted tons of references so I basically had to show her a ton of prefab art I found from other sources for pretty much every element of the illustration. Describing what I wanted and specifying that I was specifically hiring her because I wanted her to interpret that idea in her style wasn't enough. There were some issues with composition because she was trying to copy some of the references she made me provide too closely, so I actually had to draw some shitty shapes and send it to her.

I'm not complaining. She knocked it out of the park and as a person who freelances in other areas, understand that she was just trying to make sure she delivered what I wanted, but it made me realize that I could either use AI shit when I don't have the budget but need art for something, or when I do have the budget, I can at least do a pretty fantastic mockup so we can get on the same page before I tell them to go nuts.

Painters were pissed about photoshop too, but the smart ones adapted. Like it or not AI is here to stay. This generation will have to do the same.
